HOSFORD TRANSPORTATION COMPANY, a Corporation, Claimant of “G. K. WENTWORTH,” Her Engines, etc., v. FAIRFIELD STEAMSHIP CORPORATION, a Corporation, et al. No. 6773. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 19, 1932. Platt, Platt, Fales, Smith & Black, of Portland, Or., for appellant. Wood, Montague & Matthiessen, of Portland, Or., for appellees.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of proctors for respective parties. Ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
